TITLE: DOJ wants Steve Bannon jailed for 6 months for contempt of Congress, but ex-Trump aide asks for probation
SUMMARY: Federal prosecutors recommended Steve Bannon get six months in jail for defying a subpoena from the congressional probe of the Jan. 6 Capitol riot.

TITLE: Here are the top Senate races to watch in the 2022 midterms
SUMMARY: The 2022 midterm elections occur on November 8, and a handful of make-or-break races will decide which party controls the Senate. Use this guide to sort them out and learn key facts about each candidate.

TITLE: Democrats in key Senate races have more cash to spend than Republicans in the final midterm push
SUMMARY: Democrats running in key 2022 midterm Senate races, including John Fetterman and Raphael Warnock, have more cash on hand than their Republican opponents.

TITLE: TransUnion, Equifax, Experian may have violated credit reporting rules, Rep. Jim Clyburn says
SUMMARY: Rep. Jim Clyburn requested an investigation into the nation's top three credit reporting companies for allegedly failing to resolve consumer disputes.

TITLE: Schumer says he and Pelosi were 'resolute' about calling in the military to stop 'hooligans' on Jan. 6
SUMMARY: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, D-N.Y., spoke Sunday about his experience during the Jan. 6 Capitol riot.

TITLE: Democratic Sen. Mark Kelly outraises GOP opponent Blake Masters going into final weeks of midterm campaign
SUMMARY: Democratic Sen. Mark Kelly outraised Peter Thiel-backed Republican Blake Masters going into the final month of the midterm elections.

TITLE: Trump won't be the Republican nominee in 2024, ex-GOP House Speaker Paul Ryan predicts
SUMMARY: "He's not going to be the nominee, I don't think," Ryan, a former presidential running mate, said of Trump in an interview with consulting firm Teneo.

TITLE: Jan. 6 Capitol riot panel briefed on multiple calls between Secret Service and Oath Keepers, NBC News reports
SUMMARY: Oath Keepers leader Stewart Rhodes spoke to someone believed to be a Secret Service agent in advance of a Donald Trump rally in 2020, trial testimony revealed.

TITLE: Treasury's Yellen says Russia's war has weakened its economy 'for years to come'
SUMMARY: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said sanctions the U.S., the European Union and allies have levied against Russia have stunted the nation's growth prospects.

TITLE: North Korea flies warplanes near border and tests another ballistic missile
SUMMARY: Thursday's test comes less than one day after North Korea said it test-fired a long-range cruise missile.

TITLE: Supreme Court denies Trump bid to void ruling in Mar-a-Lago raid documents case
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is under criminal investigation by the Department of Justice over his removal of government documents when he left the White House.

TITLE: Jan. 6 committee votes to subpoena Trump to testify under oath about the Capitol riot
SUMMARY: The House select committee investigating the Jan. 6 Capitol riot voted to subpoena former President Donald Trump during a hearing.

TITLE: Treasury investigates whether Florida used Covid aid to fly migrants to Martha's Vineyard
SUMMARY: Treasury's Deputy Inspector General, Richard Delmar, said his office has already asked Florida for information about how it paid for the flights.

TITLE: White House is pushing ahead research to cool Earth by reflecting back sunlight
SUMMARY: There are several kinds of sunlight-reflection technology, and none have been thoroughly researched due to a perceived moral hazard. But sentiment is shifting.

TITLE: Biden's national security plan identifies Russia as imminent danger, China as long-term threat
SUMMARY: Biden outlined a plan for how the United States would "effectively compete" with China in the coming years, "while constraining a dangerous Russia."

TITLE: Some corporate leaders are funding Trump-backed election deniers in races for secretary of state, a role that administers elections
SUMMARY: Corporate leaders have been quietly bankrolling Republican candidates running to be secretaries of state while denying the results of the 2020 election.

TITLE: Judge denies Trump request to delay deposition in E. Jean Carroll rape defamation case
SUMMARY: The writer E. Jean Carroll says Donald Trump raped her in the mid-1990s in a New York City department store. The former president says she's lying.

TITLE: Warnock leads Walker, but Georgia Senate race is unchanged after abortion payment allegation, poll shows
SUMMARY: Democratic Sen. Raphael Warnock of Georgia leads Trump-backed challenger Herschel Walker by a margin of 52% to 45%, according to a Quinnipiac University poll.

TITLE: Biden threatens 'consequences' for Saudi Arabia after OPEC cut, but his options are limited
SUMMARY: What are the Biden administration's options, and could they backfire?

TITLE: No hope for the future: Economic struggles add fuel to Iran's protests
SUMMARY: Anti-government uprisings are to remain a sticking point and increase in frequency in Iran's political landscape according to Economist Intelligence Unit.

TITLE: Biden says he thinks Putin won't use nuclear weapons, but threatening to do so is 'irresponsible'
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden said he doesn't think Russian President Vladimir Putin will use nuclear weapons despite the Russian leader's repeated threats.

TITLE: Biden says he doesn't think there will be a recession, if so it will be 'very slight'
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden said he doesn't believe there will be a recession in the near future and if there is, he expects it to be a "slight" economic dip.

TITLE: Next Jan. 6 committee hearing will reveal 'pretty surprising' new material, Rep. Zoe Lofgren says
SUMMARY: The Jan. 6 panel recently interviewed the wife of Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas as part of the probe of the pro-Trump riot.

TITLE: U.S. economy is 'doing well' amid global economic uncertainty, says Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen
SUMMARY: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said the United States is doing very well despite rising energy prices, pandemic affecting global economy.

TITLE: Fake billionaire fugitive Justin Costello had gold bars, $60K in cash, Mexican pesos and phony ID when FBI nabbed him
SUMMARY: Prosecutors want Justin Costello held without bail, citing contents of a backpack FBI agents found when he was arrested on charges related to investment scams.

TITLE: Zelenskyy urges G-7 to send more weapons and impose a price cap on Russian energy exports after Russian missile strikes rock Ukraine
SUMMARY: The virtual emergency meeting was called after Russian missiles struck civilian infrastructure in a dozen Ukrainian cities.

TITLE: Treasury fines crypto company $29.3 million for violating multiple U.S. sanctions, Bank Secrecy Act
SUMMARY: Bittrex Inc. agreed to pay $29.3 million to settle civil charges that it violated U.S. sanctions and the Bank Secrecy Act.

TITLE: G-7 leaders promise to back Ukraine against Russian aggression for 'as long as it takes'
SUMMARY: Members of the G-7 reiterated their commitment to Ukraine following a virtual meeting Tuesday morning, vowing to back Ukraine for "as long as it takes."

TITLE: Biden to host fundraiser with John Fetterman in Philadelphia as Senate race with Dr. Oz tightens
SUMMARY: The Biden-Fetterman fundraiser comes as Oz, who is backed by Trump, gains ground but is still trailing the Democratic lieutenant governor.

TITLE: Israel and Lebanon reach historic agreement to resolve a long-running maritime border dispute
SUMMARY: Israel and Lebanon brokered a historic agreement to resolve a long-running maritime border dispute, following months of negotiations guided by the United States.
